                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Several words indicate that the document related to landed property and perhaps ﬁrst and foremost to taxes. Two personal names appear among the fragments, Theodoros and Nonnos. In addition, there was clearly another sheet wrapped around the main roll, but the extant letters reveal practically nothing of the contents.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">Only a strip of some ﬁve centimeters of the right side of this text survives. There might actually have been two sheets rolled together. However, they were written by the same slightly sloping, somewhat clumsy hand with a dull pen, leaving practically no right margin. Top margin ca. 4 cm (?), right margin 0–0.5 cm and bottom margin 6 cm.</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates CLIX</note>
